% Write here some information about you and your experiences
\newcommand{\PersonalDetail}{
    Paul Dirac (1902 - 1984) was a British theoretical physicist and a primary architect of quantum mechanics. Known for his extreme reticence and precise logic, he held the Lucasian Chair of Mathematics at Cambridge, a post once occupied by Newton.

    In 1928, he formulated the Dirac Equation, which successfully bridged the gap between quantum mechanics and Einstein's special relativity. This work provided a mathematical description of the electron and led to the startling prediction of antimatter.

    When the positron (the electron's antiparticle) was discovered in 1932, Dirac's theoretical brilliance was vindicated, earning him the Nobel Prize in Physics in 1933.
}



